postcontent: This is a custom matrix aerospace 7.62 (.308). So Matrix went in a partnership with Aerospace to make AR rifles. They originally sold weapons to the goverment. They are also tied to Aero precision from what i gathered from my research. Matrix Aerospace makes parts for a bunch of companies a major one is Ruger. This rifle is the DPMS pattern Upper and lower. It has an IMI buttstock. Lords nickel boron BCG. Hougue Ar10 grip. The scope is a Bushnel Bone collector 3-9×40 the scope and Leupold riser rings can be added for an additional $100. The scope is very clear and has bullet drop comp for .308. The barrel is a little bit over 18 inches the HFDF flash hider is 3.5 inches making the barrel alone roughly 21.5 inches. I am the second owner the guy who assembled it said the twist was 1/9 which is pretty low for .308. This gun could easily become a DMR. I believe this gun is 38 inches overall with the butt stock in the shortest position so long range shots are not hard at all for this firearm. The free float is octagonal with endless future options. The picitinny rail is 20 in. It has 50 rails slots that are numbered from T1 to T50 so your options are literally endless. It has a small abberations below the dust cover (as seen in pic) i have no idea what it is but it doesnt effect peformance. Bluing is 98% almost perfect. The original owner had over 1250 in it and im looking to mainly sell to fund an ak project but will entertain trade offers. I took it to the range once and that was it the scope may need to be adjusted a bit. I will sell it w/ scope 1200 without scope 1100. I have 180 in scope and rings but my loss is your gain. It will come with 1 dpms magazine. Buyer must be willing to sign bill of sale.

title: For Sale:  H&K VP9, 9mm Election Special
postcontent: In development for more than four years, the VP9 is Heckler & Koch’s latest handgun and the first striker fired HK since the popular P7 series pistols were introduced in the 1980s. Experience gained by HK engineers with the recent P30 pistol had a direct influence on the design of the VP9, but the VP9 breaks new ground with its integration of a unique striker firing system with an enhanced HK “light pull” trigger. The result is trigger quality unequaled in any production striker fired handgun. The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset.The VP9 trigger has a consistent pre-travel pull with a positive wall/crisp break. The VP9 uses HK’s ergonomic handgun grip design that includes three changeable backstraps and six side panels— accommodating all hand sizes. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. Although influenced by other HK models, the VP9 has all the hallmarks of the latest, state-of-the-art handgun. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame and the magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters. A new feature is HK’s patented charging supports on each side of the rear of the slide and provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide. The VP9’s proprietary captive flat recoil spring reduces the recoil forces affecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component service life. The VP9’s machined steel slide is protected from corrosion and wear by HK’s hostile environment finish, and of course, the entire product is backed by the H&K lifetime warranty.
